sentences.english: An elephant can uproot a tree or pick a flower without bruising a petal.
sentences.chinese: 大象能够拔起大树，或者摘下小花而不损伤花瓣。

sentences.english: Dashu knows to lower his head when he wants to get under his bed.
sentences.chinese: 大树爬进小床的时候会把头低下，匍匐前进。

sentences.english: They believe themselves to be descendants of the Great Tree, a sacred tree in the forests.
sentences.chinese: 他们相信自己是森林里的一棵圣树“大树”的子孙。

sentences.english: The sapling that bears our mark of love has grown into a big tree
sentences.chinese: 刻下爱的见证的小树，已长成大树。

sentences.english: Your boss is the point where your group attaches to the tree.
sentences.chinese: 你的顶头上司就是你们组和大树的联结点。

sentences.english: In the evening, the crestfallen little dog walked by a big tree.
sentences.chinese: 在晚上，小狗垂头丧气的在大树前乱动。

sentences.english: The roaring wind damaged a big tree.
sentences.chinese: 叫啸着的狂风把一棵大树都吹折了。

sentences.english: I cut down a big tree, and then began to make a long hole in it.
sentences.chinese: 我砍倒了一棵大树，然后开始掏成一个长条形洞。

sentences.english: The old way to grow coffee plants is under large trees.
sentences.chinese: 种咖啡树的老方法是种在大树下面。

sentences.english: They had to prop up the tree with long poles under the branches.
sentences.chinese: 他们得用长杆支着大树枝把树撑住。

sentences.english: This recumbent had established the acting industry company that enjoy the cool greatly, as before cannot have nothing worry about.
sentences.chinese: 这个靠着大树好乘凉的代工企业，依旧不能高枕无忧。

sentences.english: He rolls between two big trees.
sentences.chinese: 他在两棵大树之间滚动。

sentences.english: Do you know how to count to my age?
sentences.chinese: 你们知道怎么来数我们大树的年龄吗？

sentences.english: Witwithout learning is like a tree without fruit.
sentences.chinese: 仅无机智而无学富五车，犹如一棵大树不结果。

sentences.english: The boy lay on his back under a big tree.
sentences.chinese: 那男孩躺在一棵大树下。

sentences.english: Quite an intimating hole not just long but also with big trees on both sides of the fairway.
sentences.chinese: 几吓人的球洞，码数长之外，球道两旁都系大树。

definition: classifier for trees, cabbages, plants etc
